    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Sir
                                F. Brucé</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-09-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 19, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            been officially apprised that the Canadian authorities have paid to the
                            banks at St. Albans, in the State of Vermont, thirty-nine thousand
                                five<hi rend="smallcaps"/> hundred and twelve dollars and
                            seventy-five cents in gold, and thirty thousand and ten dollars in bank
                            notes, in compliance with an act of the Canadian parliament, on account
                            of the amount deposited with the authorities of that province upon the
                            arrest of the St. Albans marauders.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your
                            obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir Frederick W. A. Bruce,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
